    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="man_ej.00217_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener><dateline>
                <handShift rend="printed"/>
                <name type="place" rend="left">TR&#220;BNER &amp; CO</name>
                <name type="place" rend="left">AMERICAN, EUROPEAN AND ORIENTAL LITERARY AGENCY.</name>
                <name type="place" rend="right">57, &amp; 59, Ludgate Hill,</name>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">London E.C.</name>
                    <handShift rend="manuscript"/>
                    <date when="1880-07-10">July 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1880</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Walt Whitman.</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Enclosed I send you statement of <choice>
                    <abbr>a/c</abbr>
                    <expan>account</expan>
            </choice> up to date from Tr&#252;bner &amp; Co, and draft on New York for eighty
                dollars fifty cents, the amount of sales up to date.<ptr target="duk.00749_n1"/> When you get home will you
                kindly send T &amp; Co as before per JB. Lippincott &amp; Co. Philadelphia <list>
                    <item>10 "Leaves of Grass"</item>
                    <item>&amp;</item>
                    <item>5 "Two Rivulets"</item>
                </list>
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="man_ej.00220_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="man_ej.00218_large.jpg" type="recto"/>T &amp; Co as you
                will see have sold right out of "Leaves of Grass."</p>
            <p>Please tell Dr. Bucke<ptr target="n0119"/> I have received his letter <choice>
                    <sic>an</sic>
                    <corr>and</corr>
                </choice> papers for which I am obliged I shall take the earliest opportunity of
                answering his letter, as soon as I can snatch a few leisure moments.</p>
            <p>I hope you are in good health and enjoying your visit to the "Dominion".<ptr target="man.00050_n1"/> Is it, think
                you, likely
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="man_ej.00219_large.jpg" type="verso"/>to
                become a great country in spite of its severe climate?</p>
            <p>I have from time to time sent you various papers to Camden, those that may have
                reached after you left, you will probably get when you return.</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>I remain My dear</salute>
                <salute>Walt Whitman</salute>
                <salute>Yours Faithfully</salute>
                <signed>Josiah Child</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="man_ej.00136_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf003v" facs="man_ej.00137_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
